Nairobi County Governor Ann Kananu has rewarded KCPE 2021 top candidate Bruce Magata. The top candidate and his family were hosted by Kananu at the City Hall on Monday. The governor congratulated Magata and rewarded him with a cash token for being the best performer. She further wished all of the candidates that managed to score good marks in their KCPE the best in their high school education. Kananu encouraged the sitting candidates to emulate Magata. "Magata's performance is an example to be followed by other candidates awaiting their national examinations," she said. Magata hopes to join Alliance High School. "I hope to join Alliance and later pursue Robotics Engineering." He expressed gratitude to his parents for standing by him through his primary school education. Magata's mother, Brenda Makori, a City-County worker, thanked Kananu for her gracious reward and urged her for a job promotion. Makori has been in the Trade Department of the County council for ten years. Magata scored 428 out of the possible 500.